<subSubSection id="C337DD88FFF9FFE93CC8FBB2FCD3BCE8" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B928E03FFF9FFE93CC8FBB2FCD3BCE8" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="B9595211FFF9FFE93CC8FBB2FEE9BC8C" bold="true" box="[199,334,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the very prolonged head posterior to the eyes, resembling a very long giraffe-like neck. This is a unique feature within the Clavigeritae.
</paragraph>
